        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-10-21T21:33:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, I hadn\u0027t thought about the failing-to-start handler case too much. I was intending to burn everything down if crash handling fails to start, but maybe we can\u0027t/shouldn\u0027t do that.\n\nThere doesn\u0027t seem to be a huge benefit to avoiding the SetEvent() or Sleep() if the handler failed to start though? All we\u0027re bailing to is termination (just slightly sooner) since we\u0027ve already circumvented the possibility of any one else getting ahold of the process by this point.",
      "parentUuid": "fc13270f_5d046fee",
      "revId": "2d87606bb56bb00ed78ae17f334d7e65af11bcc0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
